cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper is about semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task, so cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.LG and cs.AI. The use of unsupervised foreground segmentation and graph models suggests the possibility of cs.MM. Finally, the paper mentions achieving comparable performance with state-of-the-art supervised methods, which implies the use of machine learning techniques, making cs.NE a possible sub-category as well.
